Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.12,0:01:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is a question about experience. When I saw up on the chart the different qualities of divinity, the experience of those qualities seems to be different than the experience of the functioning of allness, the oneness.\NIf the qualities are different from the functioning of the wholeness, and that's the difference in the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.32,0:01:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The wholeness and the oneness doesn't function. It is.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.02,0:01:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Isness doesn't function, doesn't do. There's no this to do with that. That's a dualistic conception.\NThe qualities of divinity are not the same as the essence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.50,0:01:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Five foot eight by 110 pounds.\NIt's not your essence, it's a quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.59,0:02:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So divinity, the feeling of it is, even the presence of love is overwhelming.\NAt the same time, infinitely powerful cannot be described.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.58,0:02:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be like describing an infinitely powerful powder puff. There's no way to really explain it.\NIt's infinitely powerful and exquisite and irresistible and omnipotent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.55,0:02:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It is omnipotent.\NYeah, it's infinitely powerful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.88,0:02:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, exquisitely loving and gentle, yeah.\NMake sure you're talking to both microphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.87,0:02:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Put them closer together, maybe, so they don't clank.\NOh, you get feedback.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.23,0:02:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NFirst, thank you for that answer to my friend's question about the anxiety, because I'm going to have to play that over and over.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.22,0:03:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NThis question has to do with a job, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a chance to pursue...\NA job that was very linear, lots of left brain material, and I decided not to because I didn't want to put all my energy into that,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.99,0:03:25.57,Default,,0,0,0,,all my focus right now, at this point, into all that left brain.\NDetail, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.21,0:03:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, can something like that actually hinder you spiritually if you don't feel inclined to go there?\NYou can't make a rule about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.20,0:03:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,At one time, forcing yourself into...\NSequential linearity could, you know, will slow down the process
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.46,0:03:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and shift your attention and energy elsewhere\Nthat might be doing better in a more non-linear awareness consciousness program, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.44,0:03:59.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo, it just depends where you are in your life and what you're...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.66,0:04:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it depends on a multitude of factors.\NI don't think it can really be answered.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.30,0:04:10.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Like, I have a stack of things in my desk at home.\NI said, I can't get into it this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.30,0:04:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a lecture Saturday.\NThat's my excuse this week.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.38,0:04:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Next week, I'll find a new excuse.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.86,0:04:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a reluctance as you get more advanced.\NThere's like a reluctance to get into linear memorization and that kind of thing
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.28,0:04:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're trying to be left brain when your energies are moving more right brain holistically.\NIt would have felt more like going to school.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.49,0:04:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.62,0:04:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see that, yeah.\NIt's a conflict, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.66,0:04:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.88,0:05:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,When I'm reading something of yours or listening to one of your lectures and I'm stuck and I know I can't understand what it is you're trying.\NThe issue is moralistic relativity and also...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.08,0:05:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,What issue is what?\NMoralistic.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.40,0:05:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm getting...\NOh, moral relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.14,0:05:21.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism, that's it.\NOh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.24,0:05:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay.\NI can't even get it, say it right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.04,0:05:37.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's pretty much a good sign that I'm suffering from it when I can't understand what you're trying to teach about it.\NSo, I'm wondering if I may have started to seek some clarity or if you can clean me up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.26,0:05:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm wondering...\NTell me what you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.52,0:05:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even know what you said.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.86,0:05:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Straighten up what?\NYou promised moral relativism?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.36,0:05:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What is your problem with moral relativism?\NIt's rather clear and obvious, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:06:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's true if I say it's true and it's not true if I say it's not true.\NAnd morality is idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.41,0:06:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an impairment of my entitlement to express myself.\NAny way I want, because we have freedom of speech.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.29,0:06:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And physical physicality is symbolic speech.\NHow do you like my freedom to choke you to death?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.58,0:06:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I got it.\NYou see what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.18,0:06:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.72,0:06:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, there's no limitation, no wall that differentiates a livable environment.\NThere's truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,At each level, there's its own truth.\NAnd so, is there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.54,0:06:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there that same moralistic...\NYeah, the MR.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.54,0:06:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The MR.\NIs that occur at each level?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.18,0:06:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Or is that...\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.05,0:06:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativism.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.68,0:07:01.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral relativism is below 200.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.45,0:07:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 200 doesn't make any sense.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.87,0:07:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThat's why the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals calibrates very low.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.84,0:07:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say, you know, we have free speech.\NIf I say, action is symbolic speech, then I'm entitled to any action I want, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.26,0:07:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Because there's no right or wrong.\NThere is no criteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.26,0:07:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,There's actually no law.\NWhat you've just done is undone the nation.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.54,0:07:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NBecause now the nation has nothing upon which to rely.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.46,0:07:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the law, then, is just merely relativism.\NI don't have to obey the law, because that's a restriction of my freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.21,0:07:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And I have freedom of expression.\NYou understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.77,0:07:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd there's absolute...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.13,0:07:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's also absolute truth.\NI mean, that's what kind of supersedes that, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.29,0:08:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what they're talking about are statements, and statements about action.\NThey're not talking about truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.61,0:08:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They're talking about moral laws.\NThey're just playing a game, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.41,0:08:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In a way?\NAn ego game?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.77,0:08:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Lewis Carroll.\NHe was a looking glass.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.49,0:08:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NThe Mad Hatter says, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.16,0:08:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it was the Mad Hatter.\NWho was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The rabbit says, when I say a word, it means what I mean it to mean.\NNothing more, nothing less.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.83,0:08:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mad Hatter.\NThe Mad Hatter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.45,0:08:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're setting yourself up almost as divinity.\NReality is what I say is reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not reality if I say it's not reality.\NSo it's the absurdity of the Mad Hatter that I pointed out to illustrate the absurdity of moral relativism.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.77,0:08:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because moral relativism says that...\Nlogic and reason are what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.10,0:09:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,An infringement of one's freedom.\NBut if all statements are questionable and untrue, then so is that statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.71,0:09:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Moral relativism has nothing to stand on because, like skepticism, it hangs itself by its own petard.\NIf there's no standard of truth, then the criticism of truth also has no standard upon which to stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.36,0:09:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's what the rabbit has to say today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.42,0:09:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mad Hatter.\NThe Mad Hatter, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.72,0:09:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mad Hatter said that?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.70,0:09:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.96,0:10:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You mentioned earlier that the chances were 1,000% easier now to reach enlightenment.\NIs it getting easier to stay physical after enlightenment than it used to be?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.45,0:10:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know about that.\NThe chances of reaching enlightenment are 1,000 times greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.70,0:10:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That we confirm many times.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.82,0:10:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.94,0:10:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.02,0:10:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.10,0:10:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.14,0:10:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.18,0:10:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.22,0:10:12.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.26,0:10:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.52,0:10:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.58,0:10:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.50,0:10:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.66,0:10:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.82,0:10:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.90,0:10:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.14,0:10:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what question to ask about it.\NI always feel, within myself, that there's like a, prior to this incarnation, there was
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.82,0:10:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,a commitment, an agreement, an understanding.\NI think I find myself holding back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.47,0:10:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Holding back what?\NFrom wanting to reach enlightenment, because I don't want to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.52,0:10:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a little work to do.\NI'm too attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.24,0:10:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Hehehe.\NHehehe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.79,0:11:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now eventually the body becomes immaterial.\NIf it keeps walking on, that's fine, and if it don't keep walking on, because you don't
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.52,0:11:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,even know what it's going to do.\NThe personal will doesn't even intervene.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.58,0:11:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I can remember walking down the aisle and turning around and didn't know whether one\Nwould get to the end or not, out of curiosity, watch what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.51,0:11:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I made 180 at the end and walked back again.\NOther times the body will breathe again or it won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.29,0:11:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's immaterial which way it goes.\NNo, if it breathes, it breathes, and if it doesn't, it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.91,0:11:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Many times I've been just waiting to die and sat there waiting to leave, and it didn't\Nhappen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.36,0:11:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Darn.\NThe smoke is shooting out from the engine on fire, the smoke behind the dashboard, you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.34,0:12:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,know.\NThere I am out, a million miles from anywhere, it's 110 out, I'm dehydrated, I've got nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.40,0:12:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,An annoyingness came from within.\NTake a screwdriver and jam it through the bottom of the glove compartment, wham.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.34,0:12:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now there's a couple of drops of coffee left in there, pour it through there.\NI poured it through there, I was just sitting there waiting to leave, it said to do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.25,0:12:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,so I did that.\NPsst, the fire went out, it was an electrical fire, and the point where I drove the car
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.20,0:12:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with the screwdriver was exactly over the fire, underneath the hood, the electrical\Ndone on my old truck over the last 30 years, it was like a mass of wires, just the left
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.00,0:12:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,brain never could attract where it was coming from.\NSo was that asked for?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.28,0:12:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.\NIt just came on to do that, and I did that, and so the body's still going.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.46,0:12:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So you surrender your life to God, surrender your body to God, surrender your life to God,\Nwhether it walks on or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.61,0:13:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been up to God.\NAnd if you have a karmic role to play, you will obviously play it, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.23,0:13:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you don't, you leave, so.\NAs I said, here's this mind right here, you know, and this guy looks at me, and we're
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.44,0:13:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at each other, he says, well, what if we don't, we can't keep it away from the\Nship?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.34,0:13:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, so we die.\NOh, he says, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.34,0:13:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The total acceptance of it, he accepted it, and then I accepted it because of my experience\Nin the snowbank.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.73,0:13:37.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the energy.\NIn the energy of the acceptance, he was able to accept it, and he said, oh, yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.94,0:13:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt's okay if you want to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.94,0:13:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can leave anything you want.\NOh, you can hang in.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.00,0:13:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter much to me.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.54,0:13:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You got permission to stay as well.\NYou don't have to feel guilty about staying.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.98,0:13:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people feel guilty that they haven't died yet.\NYou don't have to worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.98,0:13:53.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThat was a fun question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.58,0:13:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NThank you to both of you for all of the work you've done.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.58,0:13:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,On a couple of your Cs, I'm going to ask you a question.\NI'm going to ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.58,0:14:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask you a question.\NI'm going to ask you a question.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.99,0:14:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask you a question.\NOn a couple of your CDs, you mention a couple of phrases that I particularly like, like
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.94,0:14:26.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so I put them on a T-shirt for you, so, so what, and then it seemed like a good idea\Nat the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.80,0:14:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Seemed like a good idea at the time.\NThat's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.80,0:14:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThat's how you forgive yourself for everything in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.80,0:14:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed like a good idea at the time.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.62,0:14:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I also heard that you like fortune cookies.\NSo, I mean, the toy business is all electronic fortune cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.62,0:14:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I would just give it to you.\NThank you, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.62,0:14:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.62,0:14:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,My question, I apologize for it, because I know a lot of people have asked it over the\Nmonths, but I still don't quite get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.62,0:14:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And you mentioned that your time of death is preset.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.62,0:15:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And then on some of the tapes, you also talk about, you know, extreme sports or even the\Ncolleagues you knew who lived in a bubble and kept getting smaller and smaller.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.94,0:15:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The things they'd eat.\NSo, I'm a bit confused on if your time of death is set, why the extreme sports would
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.18,0:15:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,make a difference.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.18,0:15:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,What would make a difference?\NWhen you said extreme sports.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.18,0:15:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme sports.\NIf your time of death is already destined, set, then why would extreme sports make a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.43,0:15:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,difference?\NWell, the means of it is not set.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.28,0:15:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothetically, there would seem to be a disparity there, see, but if you get into a context\Nbeyond the two alternates.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.04,0:15:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You have a this versus a that, then you'll see they're both the same.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.62,0:16:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes there's a, see, the deeper the fear, the greater the length you gotta go.\NSome people have to go over Niagara Falls in a barrel to overcome that fear, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.06,0:16:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see extremes to overcome that fear.\NPeople are driven to mad, mad extremes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.14,0:16:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, some mountain where 76 people have already died.\NYou go up to that peak, and here they are at 20,000 feet with no oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.85,0:16:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm looking, and they got a coach with them.\NWhere is this coach's head taking people up there at 18,000 feet with no oxygen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.06,0:16:42.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course they're gonna get exhausted, of course they're gonna get confused, and they\Ncharge money for that as a guide?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.30,0:16:51.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I want a refund.\NI want oxygen over 10, you know, in a plane over 10,000 you get oxygen, not 18,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.99,0:16:58.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Kilimanjaro.\NHow many has Kilimanjaro killed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.35,0:17:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,How many people have died trying to climb Kilimanjaro?\NHundreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.33,0:17:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Look it up, it's sort of fun.\NSlew of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.04,0:17:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the weight of certain death, okay, let's get back and go on it.\NWould you also be willing to calibrate how much the consciousness of the group raised
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,today?\NThe consciousness of the group?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.44,0:17:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We haven't done that in a long time.\NUh, no, but I know what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.11,0:17:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the Western world.\NWe're at the level of the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.63,0:17:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How's that for erudition?\NWe're over the great books of the Western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The consciousness level of this crowd is beyond that of the great books of the Western world,\Nthe collective wisdom of mankind throughout the ages.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.20,0:17:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've evolved then into, the group has evolved into the 500s.\NThe group's gone into the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.34,0:18:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NSee, there's a couple of major jumps.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.84,0:18:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,200.\NUh, then to get out of emotionality, running your life and get to rationality at 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.80,0:18:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Then to get out of linear cause and effect, which is the Newtonian paradigm at 499.\NAnd the hardest jump is to make the jump from the 400s to the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.42,0:18:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the hardest one.\NAnd a group like this naturally, yeah, evolves into the 500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we allowed to get photos?\NYou can have a photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.00,0:18:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, come on.\NCan I stand next to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.98,0:18:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NRobert will help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.74,0:18:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's good at that.\NI want to focus.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.84,0:18:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You want, you want to be in the picture?\NCome on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.20,0:18:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See, you want to be in the picture.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.20,0:18:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my quack quack?\NWhere's my, anyway, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.77,0:18:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Doc, look at me.\NYour fortune cookie.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.77,0:18:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\NMy quack quack.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.77,0:18:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Computerized fortune cookie, yeah?\NRemember what we said the calibrated level of fortune cookies was?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.12,0:18:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.\NOh, honey, your book.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.12,0:19:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,350 or something.\NOver.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.12,0:19:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.72,0:19:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.72,0:19:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.72,0:19:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.72,0:19:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.63,0:19:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Next question.\NWell, if someone is on the spiritual path, and at the end of their life goes into a negative
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.60,0:19:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,dimension.\NWhat does that mean for the consciousness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.23,0:19:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's what?\NIn a spiritual path and at the end of their life or towards the end of their life, they
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.92,0:19:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,go into a negative...\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.46,0:19:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They fall, huh?\NWell, they would then have the karma propensities of a person at that level.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.70,0:19:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that in the so called fallen gurus.\NWho?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.11,0:19:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm thinking of one now that hit 600 and then crashed below 200.\NI'm thinking of another one that was in the 500, again crashed below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.26,0:20:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,So the great temptations come up, see?\NThe great temptations.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.16,0:20:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I said, as the Buddha called it, demons are looking through the chinks in your armor\Nto see where you're susceptible.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.89,0:20:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Vanity will give you a title, Grand Maha, Grand Mahatma.\NAnd then we'll give you swirly clothes, and we'll let people go, wah, wah, wah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.21,0:20:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that don't get you, then we'll try your money.\NWe'll pour money on you and see if that gets you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.37,0:20:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if that don't get you, how about a slinky girl who says,\Nsex is holy, let's get holy, you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.64,0:20:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So it keeps looking for a chunk, or vanity, vanity, vanity.\NIt keeps looking for where to get you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.78,0:20:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember I explained to you the knowingness that came.\NNow that you're not karmically answerable, all power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.69,0:21:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,See, because love is a constraint.\NBecause of love, you'll only go so far with people.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.34,0:21:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,But just your love of other people as fellow humans will curtail you.\NYou won't tear them to pieces with your teeth that you would below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.15,0:21:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So this was a temptation of power.\NAnd I remember, as I said, it was like a high pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.31,0:21:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see who had been through there.\NAnd I saw Jesus Christ went there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.49,0:21:26.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw exactly what he went through.\NAll power is yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.89,0:21:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is be willing to sell out integrity and honor\Nand buy stocks in the right company.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.57,0:21:47.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I was thinking about a dementia, you know, a brain.\NDementia, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.55,0:21:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that kind of deterioration.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.97,0:21:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That's of a different level.\NSee, there are levels.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.45,0:21:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the physical, mental, and spiritual.\NYou know, physicality.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.49,0:22:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Physicality would have a different karmic propensity, you know,\Nand it takes a genetic pattern, very often genetic pattern.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.61,0:22:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The person within is unaffected, you know,\Nand I used to be the only psychiatrist that would go to all the nursing homes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.09,0:22:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in Yavapai County.\NI'm away home from the girls' ranch.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.71,0:22:17.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I had all of them all the way home.\NI ever got home before dark, I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.65,0:22:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,but 30,000 miles a year running around.\NAnd the family would be all upset because mother, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.40,0:22:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,was forgetful and all this, didn't recognize me.\NWell, that's their ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.00,0:22:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It just got hurt.\NI'd say, mother, how is it here?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.59,0:22:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, they're very nice to me.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.15,0:22:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, do they treat you well?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.79,0:22:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to be someplace else?\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.97,0:22:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I think this is just fine.\NShe's perfectly at serenity and peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.12,0:22:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and I always feel like the spirit is already half gone over.\NIf she were agitated, would that be a different?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.68,0:22:55.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Agitation would be a different thing.\NIt would be a reaction to it, and therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.92,0:23:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you could treat the agitation, yes.\NYou're wondering about the karmic implications of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.27,0:23:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.05,0:23:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to do a little research on it.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.13,0:23:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt that your spiritual destiny is going to be determined\Nby the linear physicality of its expression.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.28,0:23:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAs long as we remember who we are, we're okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.94,0:23:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember that you're you.\NSomebody says, who am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.84,0:23:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, I'm me.\NOh, you pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.67,0:23:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the test of the cat.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.76,0:23:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I've had this discussion with you lots of times.\NYou just haven't been there, so I thought I'd bring it up now.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.02,0:23:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?\NWhat discussion?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.76,0:23:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind of back to what the lady brought up before\Nabout the day of our death, our physical death,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.64,0:24:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is written the day we're born.\NIt's not written.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.01,0:24:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It's recorded?\NHow do I think of it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.49,0:24:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a tape.\NIf you get a tape of a movie,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.01,0:24:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the end of the movie is already on the tape.\NIt's not an infinite tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.73,0:24:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't go on forever.\NSo every movie has a terminal point.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.84,0:24:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's sequential.\NAfter this event, this event, this event.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.74,0:24:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after this event, that's the end of the movie.\NWith that in mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.51,0:24:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep wondering about our preoccupation\Nwith this physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.11,0:24:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look at what we like to term disasters,\Nwe have a natural disaster and a thousand people die.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.49,0:24:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We have buildings fall in New York\Nand thousands of people die.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.65,0:24:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If those occasions hadn't arisen,\Nwouldn't all of those people have died from a heart attack
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.01,0:24:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or something that day?\NIt's a hypothetical.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.48,0:24:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if that's a good question.\NI don't know that I can answer it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.48,0:24:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I see it more like group karma,\Nthat it's not by accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.48,0:24:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember the bridge of St. Louis Ray?\NWhy were those, what was it, six people or so and so,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.48,0:25:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,crossing the bridge when it collapsed?\NWhy those six people out of all the civilizations?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.48,0:25:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic propensity and influences are hard to explain\Nwithin a logical, linear way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.73,0:25:18.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They're subtle and more inferential.\NYou just happen to be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.73,0:25:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,where those things happen.\NYou know, you could ask what is the karmic destiny
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.95,0:25:29.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of somebody whose house blows down in a hurricane\Nand immediately they rebuild it in exactly the same place.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.46,0:25:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,California coast, the mudslides.\NOne expensive house after another falls down.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.23,0:25:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's not that it's a specific day\Nthese people are going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.23,0:25:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was after a series of events that they were killed.\NI think it's more the fulfillment of a story than a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.23,0:25:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I have permission to ask this.\NIt's the fulfillment of the story that brings the story to the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.23,0:25:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah, that's a good question.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.23,0:25:59.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Cool.\NSo it's not stamped into like a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.23,0:26:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd if I might, one more.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.03,0:26:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If in fact there's no cause and effect,\Nwhat are we taking responsibility for
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.38,0:26:15.38,Default,,0,0,0,,when we're taking responsibility not for only what we do\Nbut previous lives that we didn't cause?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.38,0:26:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that you're the source, let's say.\NNot the cause, but you're the source.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.08,0:26:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we share the karmic consequences of that\Nwhich we cheer on and align with.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.10,0:26:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're a proponent of bullfighting,\Nthen you share somewhat the karmic consequence
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.39,0:26:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,of that which okays cruelty to animals for amusement.\NWith the bullfighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.42,0:26:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what are they getting out of the bullfight?\NAmusement.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.84,0:26:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,An amusing afternoon for you, but not for the bull, yeah?\NAnd often not for the matador either.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.84,0:27:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless they adopt children afterwards.\NThat's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.18,0:27:12.18,Default,,0,0,0,,On several occasions now,\Nwhile doing A Course in Miracle lessons,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.18,0:27:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I hear a voice and my question is whether or not\NI should completely ignore this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.18,0:27:19.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean here? Auditory?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.27,0:27:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What kind of things does it say to you?\NOn a couple of occasions,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.70,0:27:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's kind of pointing me to read something\Nor go someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.70,0:27:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And other times it's maybe more fearful things.\NIt's like an inner voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.70,0:27:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NBut it's experienced as though it's auditory.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.90,0:27:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.25,0:27:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see what we can figure that is.\NThat is...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.11,0:27:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I intuit what it is.\NMm-hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.10,0:27:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWhat I'm holding is correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.20,0:27:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt's a segmentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.20,0:28:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a segmentation off of a piece of the personality.\NI'd own it back as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.26,0:28:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Should I put faith in what I hear\Nor just kind of observe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.98,0:28:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NIt's got nothing to do with what the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.98,0:28:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NIt has to do with the phenomena.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.98,0:28:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo I have permission to ask this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.53,0:28:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a dissociated aspect of its own personality.\NIt's a dissociated aspect of your own personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.56,0:28:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a separate self?\NLike you've separated off from it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.56,0:28:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,as though it is not you.\NI get it's a dissociated small little part
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.51,0:28:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,of your personality.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.28,0:28:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd have to see in the office.\NYou'd have to lay down on the couch
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.28,0:28:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in a couple of years and figure it out.\NWhy you, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.28,0:28:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI think the way I heal it is I would deny
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.98,0:28:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that it's separate from yourself\Nand own it that it is yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.98,0:28:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And just as...\NBecause even if you heard it through another voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.98,0:28:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's what you're holding in mind\Nthat's sounding back to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.98,0:29:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be a dissociated thought\Nthat you don't want to own, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.85,0:29:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So is it as much of an unreality\Nas everything else that goes on in one's mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.85,0:29:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no more real nor unreal\Nthan anything else that goes on in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.30,0:29:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You have dreams, right?\NThat doesn't mean you're loony.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.30,0:29:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just meaning you're having a dream.\NSo you're having an auditory dream while you're awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.30,0:29:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.94,0:29:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOwn it back as a portion of your own personality.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.94,0:29:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's, you know, that that is also me.\NJust as your dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.67,0:29:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't disown your dreams.\NWhose dreams are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.67,0:29:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Waking dream.\NWaking auditory dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.22,0:29:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Waking auditory dream.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.66,0:29:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.66,0:29:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.\NThat is quick diagnosis.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.88,0:29:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,My goodness.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.09,0:30:01.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for giving this opportunity to come\Nand be able to say how grateful we are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.55,0:30:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to all that you've given to us.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.06,0:30:10.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wonderful gift to have this time with you.\NI was interested today as you were talking about,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.74,0:30:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you were talking about spiritual teachers\Nand I was, came to mind Victor Frankl
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.93,0:30:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and his experience,\Nof having to, having, being able to find grace
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.09,0:30:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in the middle of hell\Nand how that relates to your experience of finding grace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.22,0:30:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Victor Frankl ended up writing a book.\NHe was at a concentration camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.22,0:30:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NAnd he wrote about an aspect of psychology
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.05,0:30:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that was really very important\Nand I can't specifically give you the exact name of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.05,0:30:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Logos, wasn't it?\NThat's maybe not the book but the concept.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.05,0:30:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Logos therapy.\NWell, that's not what it was about.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.12,0:31:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe the title of the book was Man's Search for Meaning.\NIs that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.12,0:31:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.12,0:31:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat looking for meaning is instinctual.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.25,0:31:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of the instincts.\NFreud did not mention it as an instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.25,0:31:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,He said it's sufficiently powerful\Nand I think that's true
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.25,0:31:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,because when we talk about spiritual fantasy,\Nsee, it's like people are always looking for meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.25,0:31:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and if they can't find meaning, they'll invent one.\NMan wants to know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.64,0:31:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you get together the facts,\Nbut what do they mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.64,0:31:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yes, I liked Frankl\Nand it was like the will to meaning is instinctual
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.77,0:31:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and I agreed with him for the more advanced.\NBut you see, even primitive man wanted to know
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.25,0:31:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the meaning of a volcano?\NHe invented angry gods and sacrificed maidens.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.60,0:32:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the meaning of natural phenomena?\NYou know, kinda like the problems and the problems and the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.30,0:32:05.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Was that experience for him\Nof finding love and ultimate love in the middle of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.30,0:32:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,similar to the experience you had\Nin finding God in the middle of hell
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.68,0:32:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or was it a different experience?\NOh, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.68,0:32:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, his was an external hell.\NMine was internal.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.67,0:32:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But internally, he experienced probably the same.\NExtreme, extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.10,0:32:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\Nand I've forgotten about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.55,0:32:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Dr. Frankel wrote that man has an instinctive drive\Nto discern meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.75,0:32:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Meaning.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.98,0:32:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you both.\NI have a very hard question for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.14,0:32:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I have intuited that some physical challenges\Nthat have come up are a karmic undoing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.02,0:33:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But my question is,\Nif I surrender the guilt
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.12,0:33:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask for a miracle to have the guilt removed,\Nis that the right spiritual path to take
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.16,0:33:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,or do I need to unwork the karma?\NHow to process it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.78,0:33:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I would work on all levels simultaneously.\NI'd pray for a miracle to see it as it is in truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.43,0:33:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I would also,\NI would also pray for whatever the negative side of this is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.05,0:33:37.41,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself.\NAssume it's something within yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.64,0:33:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And pray for the opposite of that,\Nparadoxically, to undo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.89,0:33:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And keep reaffirming that you're an infinite being\Nand you're only subject to what you hold in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.51,0:34:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And forgive yourself for whatever it is.\NI felt like it wasn't just my own guilt,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.95,0:34:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,but that I had an unforgiveness\Nfrom someone stabbing me in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.31,0:34:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAnd back in a past life.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.05,0:34:12.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And the betrayal of that\Nwas such a heart pain
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.50,0:34:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that I haven't been able to let that go.\NBetrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.12,0:34:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, betrayal.\NAnd it wasn't the physical death,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.46,0:34:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,but the betrayal.\NNo, it was the betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.66,0:34:22.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NAll right, so you can undo the betrayal.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.00,0:34:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Think what Jesus Christ must have felt\Nwhen he was kissed by a friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.27,0:34:35.79,Default,,0,0,0,,So you share, you see,\Nhow Christ suffered for all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.60,0:34:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Betrayal by a trusted friend.\NYeah, pray for the forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.86,0:34:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of the one in you who betrays others.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.63,0:34:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dr. Hawkins.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.89,0:35:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How does one best dissolve the duality\Nbetween oneself and God?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.23,0:35:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't a duality.\NThat's a linguistic event you just recorded.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.86,0:35:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no duality between oneself and God.\NBut it seems that oneself is so small
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.57,0:35:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in comparison to God.\NThe personal self.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.92,0:35:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NYes, the personal self is small.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.27,0:35:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they call it the small self.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.76,0:35:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not a disparity.\NIt's not a disparity.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.69,0:35:48.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like you are already within that\Nand have set up some falsity
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.91,0:35:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you don't realize\Nthat you are at one with the one,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.04,0:35:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're separate from the one.\NYou know, it's like,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.97,0:35:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,it just takes constant spiritual work\Nof one kind or another
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.97,0:36:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and then eventually that falls away.\NIs it a matter of seeing oneself as limited?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.16,0:36:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Discrete, yeah.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.61,0:36:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NLast month,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.34,0:36:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you were talking about\Nthe Buddha came to teach us enlightenment,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.76,0:36:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,but Jesus came to teach us salvation.\NCan you talk a little bit about
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.74,0:36:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,what you mean by salvation?\NSalvation means that you,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.26,0:36:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,in and of yourself,\Nhaven't earned enough positive karma
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.34,0:36:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to enter the kingdom of heaven.\NTherefore, by your commitment to your teacher,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.25,0:36:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,your teacher then becomes your advocate\Nbefore God at the right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.15,0:36:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He speaks for you.\NAnd she is dedicated to the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.21,0:37:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I will speak for her.\NAnd therefore, you're admitted
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.63,0:37:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's so,\Nit's the same in the Lotus Land Buddhism
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.02,0:37:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,where an aspect of the Buddha\Nis actually the Buddha.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.74,0:37:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your savior.\NThat you can get to this realm
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.21,0:37:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and the savior then speaks for you.\NThat you, in and of yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.21,0:37:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,unaided, don't have enough karmic momentum\Nto enter that celestial domain, celestial.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.88,0:37:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're asking to enter the celestial.\NThe celestial can be entered
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.86,0:37:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,if you are under the tutelage of a master.\NThe savior then acts differently
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.69,0:37:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,than enlightenment.\NEnlightenment on your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.37,0:37:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI will speak for you before the father
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.52,0:37:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at the right hand of the father\Nbecause of your dedication to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.65,0:37:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NDr. Hawkins,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.01,0:38:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,when you speak of forces that are hostile to us,\Nto an enlightened seeker
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.82,0:38:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,or a seeker of enlightenment.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.98,0:38:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It kicks back in me\Nto old Christian teachings
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.70,0:38:16.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that I judged were fear-based\Nbeing hostile beings.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.01,0:38:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Demons, possession, that type of stuff.\NIs that what you're talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.50,0:38:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And if so, are there practical defenses\Nthat we who are not enlightened yet
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.28,0:38:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,can take or should take?\NYou just follow your spiritual path.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.51,0:38:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, like I say, power over the world,\Npower over the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.73,0:38:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,is lost as integrity takes,\Nas integrity gets more and stronger
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.07,0:38:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and stronger,\Nthan as you saw on Wall Street,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.69,0:39:03.49,Default,,0,0,0,,real calm when all of them began to fall.\NTherefore, they would consider integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.49,0:39:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,to be their enemy\Nbecause it would be their unmasking.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.65,0:39:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be whipping the sheep's clothing\Noff the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.15,0:39:14.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NSo this is more internal
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.72,0:39:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,as far as...\NThis isn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.22,0:39:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I know what you're talking about.\NIt's enough to make you paranoid.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.91,0:39:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.48,0:39:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That's interesting.\NWhat you're talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.88,0:39:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,is the paranoia, the paranoid fear.\NThat as you reach a higher and higher level,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.96,0:39:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is...\NIt attracts that which is your antithesis
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.28,0:39:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and attack it\Nbecause it feels threatened by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.09,0:39:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, falsehood feels threatened by truth.\NThat is so.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.14,0:39:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And the more it feels threatened,\Nthe more vociferous it gets,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.40,0:39:55.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the louder it yells,\Nand the more savagely it attacks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.50,0:39:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that not so?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.82,0:40:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,How popular is...\NHow popular is it to quote from the Constitution
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.42,0:40:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that Congress shall make no law\Nprohibiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.02,0:40:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,No, establishing religion\Nnor prohibiting the free exercise thereof?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.90,0:40:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How popular is the last half of that sentence?\NI haven't heard a one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.67,0:40:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the conservative religious people\Nquote the Constitution correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.56,0:40:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit the free exercise thereof.\NI mean, can't they read English?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.06,0:40:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know,\Nyou see,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.12,0:40:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,if I choose to emphasize that,\Nget to be a blogger,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.44,0:40:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,blog it all over the place,\Nwrite letters to everybody,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.78,0:40:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll arouse that which is hostile to that viewpoint.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.44,0:41:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Nor prohibit the free exercise thereof.\NSanta Claus.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.70,0:41:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?\NDr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.52,0:41:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The study group that I belong to\Nhas been...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.87,0:41:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,focusing on prayer.\NAnd there's an old saying
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.79,0:41:28.33,Default,,0,0,0,,that we should pray\Nas though everything depends upon God
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.33,0:41:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and work as though everything depends upon us.\NAnd how does that calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.03,0:41:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a neat saying.\NWhat's the first part of the sentence again?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.58,0:41:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You pray as though everything depends upon God.\NYes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.22,0:42:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You're totally dependent on God, yes.\NYes, work as though everything depended on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.59,0:42:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NPut forth your most effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.55,0:42:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know what that quote calibrates that?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.93,0:42:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NWe have permission to quote that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.42,0:42:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over 350,\N380,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.40,0:42:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,390,\N400,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.44,0:42:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,395,\N400,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.80,0:42:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,395.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.86,0:42:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it change if,\Ninstead of saying work as though everything depends upon us,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.54,0:42:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,to say be,\Nto be,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.45,0:42:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,does that alter the...\NDoes it change?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.31,0:42:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The call it calibration to be because to work is to do and to do calibrates lower than to be from...\NIt doesn't really matter what it calibrates.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.88,0:42:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't.\NNo, it's integrous.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.88,0:42:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NIt's taking responsibility at the same time acknowledging the sovereignty of God.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.08,0:43:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a very excellent saying, I think.\NAll right, thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.93,0:43:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's similar to the 12-step group say, you know,\Nyou're responsible for the effort, but not the result.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.34,0:43:19.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're accountable for the effort.\NThe result is up to an altitude of forces, karmic and otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.24,0:43:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat you can't have anything to do with it, but you're karmically rewarded by having done the best you can,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.72,0:43:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,so far as you see your responsibility, yeah?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.25,0:43:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NThank you, Susan.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.25,0:43:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.03,0:43:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NDr. Hawkins, in truth versus falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.28,0:44:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you included a chart calibrating ancient societies.\NThe ones that calibrated by far the highest was Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.50,0:44:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When and where was Atlantis?\NNo, I didn't calibrate the level of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.50,0:44:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I calibrated Atlantis was an actual reality rather than a fantasy.\NIt says it was a reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.53,0:44:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou said it was a 295.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.63,0:44:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Did I?\NI don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.86,0:44:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right here.\NHistorical societies.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.82,0:44:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It calibrated 290, yes.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.22,0:44:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm-hmm.\NJust...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.22,0:44:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it did exist.\NThat's what we...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.42,0:44:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NIn fact, we got a confirmation of its location, even.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.72,0:44:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NAnd that was where?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.32,0:44:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget now.\NIs it...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.16,0:44:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I think they closed up now.\NI don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.96,0:44:48.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it a very ancient society?\NI mean, before our recorded history, or is it...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.46,0:44:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Before our recorded history, well, don't forget Plato.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.06,0:44:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYou know, recounted the history of Atlantis.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.56,0:44:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.56,0:44:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There is much...\NEvidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.76,0:45:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And we did calibrate.\NThere was research that indicated its location.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.75,0:45:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And I forget where that location was.\NThere were several provisional locations.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.85,0:45:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,They were not correct.\NBut there was one they did get the other correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.65,0:45:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I forget.\NThe Greek isle someplace.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.95,0:45:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We weren't supposed to share it.\NThat's what...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.45,0:45:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.75,0:45:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry about the question.\NI didn't know anything about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.45,0:45:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo, we got...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.45,0:45:24.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn't share it, but...\NOh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.60,0:45:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.90,0:45:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.54,0:45:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're thinking of the...\NYou're thinking of Cayce.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.30,0:45:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Cayce's readings on Atlantis.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.10,0:45:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.26,0:45:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But I mean, we got...\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.46,0:45:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NI got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.46,0:45:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NHi.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.76,0:45:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is in regards to the evolution of human consciousness and in regards to\Ngroup.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.96,0:45:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You say that we come all in together and sometimes we leave together.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.36,0:45:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It sort of is.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.96,0:45:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So, with realms ranging from the lower astrals all the way up to the celestial realms, what's\Nthe difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.46,0:45:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.76,0:45:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.96,0:46:00.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NYeah.
