Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.39,1:07:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to question and he's really on the subject of fear and anxiety and was\Ncoming up for me recently is there's there's really no thinking going on but
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.65,1:08:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,there's that general sort of program it's sort of beneath conscious awareness\Nthat seems to you running I've seen you becoming more aware of it and it seems
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.99,1:08:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to be happening in our study group is a number of people the same things\Nhappening for subliminal thinking this subliminal thinking the direct reality
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.71,1:08:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,a little yeah it's outside of awareness it's not like there's sort of a silence there but yet\Nthere's still this anxiety and this leads to the root of my question is that in the root chakra
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.06,1:08:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,really or I guess perhaps I have this I guess for the past several years I've had this sort of\Nenlarged prostate it's benign but it just seems to never it just seems to constantly be there and I
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.18,1:08:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,have a feeling it's sort of related to this fear or this anxiety and I'm wondering if you could\Ntalk to me about that if there is a correlation potentially there I don't know other than we tend
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.82,1:09:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to manifest what's held in mind if you didn't have an enlarged prostate but I tell you watch\Ntelevision you will diagrams I want to take for it so the suggestion is already imprinted so when
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.66,1:09:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,we talk about the collective\Nwe're really talking about imprinting how long does it take to program you you just got programmed
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.36,1:09:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that fast that's why the mind is innocent it can't look over and decide gee is that a healthy thought\Nthat I want to entertain it already got the image you know the prostate photo diagram on TV you know
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.62,1:09:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen enough of it there it is right didn't have before you got it now so all you can do is\Nnegate it that it doesn't apply to you that you're an infinite being
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.94,1:09:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only subject to what you hold in mind and that you're not subject to this belief system that\Nall men get prostate trouble as they get older okay now is it in any way related to just generalized
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.48,1:10:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,sort of anxiety or fear because certainly in the literature some of the things you can look up from\Nthe net saying you know maybe what certain emotional positions as a consequence is holding
Dialogue: 0,1:10:03.92,1:10:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,certain positions you get an enlarged prostate like generalized fear or you know giving up oh\Nyou get a thousand amateurish ideas about it
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.74,1:10:25.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's the thought held in mind is a belief system breast cancer I mean all these things that afflict\Nmankind are part of the collective so once they're held in the collective they're given the authority
Dialogue: 0,1:10:25.22,1:10:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,of multiple agreement well now they got great power you know okay so it's really bad any sort\Nof a relationship I've created it's best to sort of like I don't think it's individual I think you
Dialogue: 0,1:10:35.54,1:10:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,just have to negate that you yourself are an infinite being and you're only subject to what\Nyou hold in mind and you hereby declare that that's invalid
Dialogue: 0,1:10:42.74,1:10:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,ok thank you meantime take your flumax\Nno I did
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.86,1:11:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,hello sir thanks for the talk today yeah my question I'm working on surrendering all my\Nmeaningless thoughts as they come up and i've been doing it for a while ever since I got ran
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.40,1:11:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,into your teaching and\NI've been pretty consistent with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.92,1:11:22.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the main things that I have trouble with\Nis surrendering my positionalities that I create
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.10,1:11:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,in regard to spiritual teaching.\NAnd I don't know why that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.29,1:11:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't seem to get past it.\NI pray about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.11,1:11:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes because it seems important.\NAnd my spiritual knight had difficulty with that too.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.15,1:11:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,False teachings.\NIndignation would come up.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.15,1:11:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you mislead people\Nand take them out to these fantasy lands
Dialogue: 0,1:11:45.97,1:11:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and take their money\Nand watch them destroy themselves?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.71,1:11:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,These cults, they all committed suicide at the same time\Nbecause they hail a bop comment or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:55.03,1:12:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hard to know about that\Nand not feel your gorge sort of rise with indignation.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:00.63,1:12:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How people could trick people into following them through\Njust for the sake of personal power.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.52,1:12:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The cults.\NBut I think that's a natural phase we go through.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.20,1:12:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, that way you face that you do hold good and evil\Nand that it's real.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.74,1:12:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not just a conceptual\Nbecause you can feel indignation rise in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:25.31,1:12:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What about like, sometimes I just like,\Nwithin, like I'll have a talk with another spiritual student
Dialogue: 0,1:12:32.09,1:12:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and say they're doing the Course in Miracles\Nand then like maybe I'll just have a disagreement
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.75,1:12:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I just constantly relive the conversation over and over again.\NI guess because it's important to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.63,1:12:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to arrive at the truth.\NSo you just ask God to help you find what is the truth
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.01,1:12:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and to recontextualize the argument for you.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:52.21,1:12:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NOkay, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.69,1:12:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's natural.\NI mean, if you're committed to spirituality,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.39,1:13:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you get into spiritual doubt, argument, discourse, disagreement.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.82,1:13:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,About four or five months ago,\Nwe formed a little group to work for God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:14.79,1:13:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And then two months ago, your name just kept coming up.\NAnd up and up.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.35,1:13:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'm here.\NOur goal is to use technology to help shift human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:28.73,1:13:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And having read your book, Eye of the Eye,\Nthe 78% that are below 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.66,1:13:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to use some sort of technology to...\NTechnology?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.62,1:13:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThat's linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.72,1:13:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut can that be used to help...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.70,1:13:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,People that are below 200?\NAnd if not,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.43,1:13:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what do you recommend to help that...\NThe other population come up?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:57.60,1:14:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender the world to God?\NSurrender...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.32,1:14:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The world to God.\NThe world to God from them or from us?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:10.08,1:14:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We all do what we can,\Ndepending on...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.84,1:14:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, whatever level of your consciousness.\NYou will see the requirements are different
Dialogue: 0,1:14:18.58,1:14:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,at this level than this level.\NThis level, you're required...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:21.62,1:14:25.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're required to do something about it.\NThis required level, you're required not to do something about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:26.33,1:14:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This level, you don't see there's anything that needs to be done about anything\Nbecause karmically, and by the nature of evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.33,1:14:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,human consciousness is going up like that, you see, without you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.94,1:14:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And so do we...\NSo you see, it's going up like so.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.72,1:14:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,However, you could assist in the evolution.\NAssist.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.22,1:14:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and that was our goal.\NAnd so we were going to use technology as well as any other means.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:51.90,1:14:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And if the technology doesn't work,\Nis there anything else that you could recommend that we...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.72,1:15:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, surrender the world to God, yes.\NLet God worry about the evolution of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.91,1:15:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so do we...\NDo anything...
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.00,1:15:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Education.\NEducation, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.29,1:15:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So recommend...\NFor all of mankind, education, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.29,1:15:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I think of all the things that people can do for others,\Neducation is the only one that works.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:21.71,1:15:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So provide education so that they could...\NEducation is the only thing that works.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.89,1:15:29.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NThere's no point in giving poor people money
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.05,1:15:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because they will probably get poor all over again.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:32.05,1:15:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they know how to handle money, they wouldn't be poor.\NSo you're giving it to their own person.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.78,1:15:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What you want to do is provide the circumstances for them to thrive.\NAnd research education is the greatest, the greatest benefit.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.07,1:15:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Every dollar spent on education more than pays for itself.\NSo there is no technology available from your experience, exposure,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:54.30,1:16:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that has done any helping of anything...\NI don't know of any technology.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:00.30,1:16:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:02.33,1:16:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, thank you very much.\NThe steam engine, maybe.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:11.25,1:16:14.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The water wheel.\NThe wheel.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.25,1:16:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, by God, the wheel.\NYou're right, Steve.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.47,1:16:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The wheel.\NWell, I want to thank you for all that you do
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.47,1:16:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and thank you for answering so many questions.\NI had a, you know, kind of a feeling or a knowingness that I came upon
Dialogue: 0,1:16:29.47,1:16:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a week or so ago, and I just wanted to discuss it\Nor see what you had to say with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.50,1:16:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And the idea is that I felt that if I'm able to transcend\Nthis material experience form, if I transcend this form,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:46.63,1:16:54.43,Default,,0,0,0,,am I transcending all form at the same time?\NIf you transcend form as form, transcend the non-linear,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.43,1:16:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you're at 850.\NYep.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.43,1:17:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you don't have to worry about it\Nbecause it has no reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.42,1:17:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't like you have to decline it.\NIt's not an option.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.47,1:17:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:28.57,1:17:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I am a psychology student in Flagstaff,\Nand I was a little surprised that Freud calibrates at 499.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.57,1:17:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?\NOh, Freud, yes, 499, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.57,1:17:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And then today when you had the slides up,\Nso Freud calibrates higher than what?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.57,1:17:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,William James or Shakespeare.\NAnd I know you said it means not better than.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:52.57,1:17:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see, what is your question again?\NWell, the question...
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.57,1:18:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,She wants to know why that Freud is at 499.\NFreud calibrated at 499, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.57,1:18:04.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the next thing?\NHe said he calibrated higher than Shakespeare.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.57,1:18:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Same thing.\NOh, I can't compare it with...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.57,1:18:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't compare apples and oranges.\NWell, my question is, does that mean I have to hold
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.57,1:18:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud's ideas with so much truth?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.70,1:18:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Because a lot of his...\NYou can't compare it to...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:18.70,1:18:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Who was the other person?\NI have no idea who you're comparing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.70,1:18:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute.\NI'm not comparing him.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:22.70,1:18:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You said Freud at 499 and what?\NShe's just...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.70,1:18:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean I have to hold his...\NNo, no, who was the other person she compared him to?
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.70,1:18:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,William James.\NWilliam James.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.70,1:18:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,William James, he was 490.\NAnd that, you know, surprised me, but then...
Dialogue: 0,1:18:32.70,1:18:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,These are different levels that they're expressing, see?\NFreud, like Einstein.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.73,1:18:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein is also at 499.\NAlso Sir Isaac Newton.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.73,1:18:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All geniuses...\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.73,1:18:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,...took the level of genius to the ultimate.\NThen you've got to jump paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.73,1:18:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So does this mean I have to...\NSo at 499, Einstein said,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:54.04,1:19:02.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I prefer to believe that there's an independent objective universe out there\Nthat exists independent of human consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.04,1:19:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And he rejected 500.\NBecause at 500, you move from the linear Newtonian paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.04,1:19:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to subjectivity as the ultimate reality.\NI don't live within symbols.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.04,1:19:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I live within subjective experiential.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.04,1:19:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That's over 500, see?\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.04,1:19:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So does that...\NI guess I find so many of Freud's ideas nuts and...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:26.33,1:19:30.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You find Freud's ideas nuts?\NSo many of Freud's ideas I find nuts.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.33,1:19:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean as a concept?\NOh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.33,1:19:36.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Experientially, you ever go through a Freudian psychoanalysis?\NYou'll see how...
Dialogue: 0,1:19:36.33,1:19:39.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll find out different.\NI guess that's my point then.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.33,1:19:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, do I hold Freud as a genius like Einstein?\NHe is a genius, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.33,1:19:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYou see, you're too young to realize that.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.55,1:19:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NYou're too young to realize the impact he had on all generations.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.55,1:19:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud's discoveries of the unconscious turned everything around.\NHad a major impact.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.51,1:20:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Changed the whole paradigm of responsibility, sexuality, intention.\NJust like the women's revolution of becoming equal with men.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:08.99,1:20:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It just changes the whole thing.\NIt's just a whole different way of holding value and the...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.28,1:20:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud's main genius was in discovering the unconscious.\NAnd the powerful effect that it has in the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.28,1:20:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that the unconscious is unconscious.\NWell, Carl Jung was...
Dialogue: 0,1:20:27.57,1:20:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Carl Jung was 520.\NWell, Carl Jung also explored the unconscious, but he included the spiritual as a reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:33.57,1:20:35.57,Default,,0,0,0,,whereas Freud did not.\NThat's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.57,1:20:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Freud looked at the anthropomorphic God and said, because God is traditionally depicted\Nas anthropomorphic, obviously a projection of man's own unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.07,1:20:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he made the invalid conclusion, therefore God doesn't exist.\NNo, he should have said, therefore the irrational, you know, in my own writings,
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.58,1:21:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I reject the anthropomorphic depictions of God as primitive projection from the, you know,\Nprimitive onto divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.58,1:21:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,God makes the volcanoes, God makes the earthquakes, you know.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.35,1:21:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So put Carl Jung on the pedestal.\NCarl Jung.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.35,1:21:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not up there.\NFreud discovered the unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.35,1:21:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his main discovery and the power of the unconscious.\NAnd then Jung carried it further and included it.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.35,1:21:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He included the spiritual dimension.\NIt was Jung that discovered synchronicity.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.35,1:21:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It was because of Carl Jung's honesty that the whole 12-step movement arose.\NWithout Carl Jung, Bill W. never would have gotten this over, nor would have anybody who
Dialogue: 0,1:21:39.67,1:21:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,preceded him.\NYeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.67,1:21:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a psychology student, huh?\NOh, that's a fun trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.67,1:21:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It is.\NIt sure is.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.67,1:21:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,God help you, woman.\NThe jungle of psychology, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.67,1:22:07.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All the different theories and, yeah.\NDr. Hawkins, before I have heard you speak about how one could own a quality of God,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.38,1:22:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,be that quality kindness or politeness or love or another quality, is owning a quality\Nof God the same as contemplating on that quality?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.38,1:22:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NContemplating it, realizing it that is innate within yourself as well.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.95,1:22:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That that quality that we call divine is intrinsic to yourself also.\NA mouse got caught in a mouse trap, you know, a sticky pad.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.74,1:22:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't come to the lecture until I went out and relieved the mouse of the slow torture\Nof slowly dying of suffocation and starvation and dehydration from the quick mercy death.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.67,1:22:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't stand the thought that he's going to be left there to suffer and suffer and\Nsuffer.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.02,1:22:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, that's also something you could let go of and say you're just projecting\Nthat onto the mouse.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.11,1:22:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see how you handled it?\NIs it merciful to put him to sleep?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.11,1:23:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it more merciful to let it be?\NShould I surrender him to God?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.24,1:23:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's God's problem if this mouse lays there and takes two weeks to die of dehydration,\Nright?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.24,1:23:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the simplest thing.\NIt's how you hold it, how you see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.24,1:23:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NI surrendered it to God and put it out of its misery.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.24,1:23:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, God has to do it.\NHe has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.24,1:23:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to do it.\NHe has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.24,1:23:12.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to do it.\NHe has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.37,1:23:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to do it.\NHe has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.37,1:23:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to do it.\NHe has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.48,1:23:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to do it.\NHe has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.48,1:23:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,He has to do it.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:23.41,1:23:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I surrendered it to God and put it out of its misery.\NWell, God has to act through somebody.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.14,1:23:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, for God's sake, put him to sleep.\NI'm like, mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.14,1:23:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Good night.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:31.14,1:23:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Move along quickly now.\NYes?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:33.14,1:23:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi.\NI had no idea that you would be so funny, so I was glad.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.63,1:23:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Paramahansa Yogananda, he called enlightenment superconscious.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:58.63,1:24:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,He called enlightenment superconscious union with God.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.63,1:24:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And sleep, deep, deep dreamless sleep, subconscious union with God.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.63,1:24:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And encouraged his disciples to meditate as much as possible.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.63,1:24:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And sleep as little as possible.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.63,1:24:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm wondering what you think about that instruction, whether that does, in fact, increase\Nthe possibility or the nature of the waking state toward the extension.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.63,1:24:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The intention behind it, of course, is to meditate as much as possible.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.70,1:24:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And some spiritual divisions try to cut down on physical sleep.\NI don't notice that there's any benefit one way or the other, frankly.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.74,1:24:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NDo you ever visit the center there in California?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.77,1:24:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I haven't been there, no.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.77,1:24:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NAutobiography of a Yogi, he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.02,1:24:54.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NVery famous book.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.38,1:24:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We're almost at the end.\NThank you, Dr. Hawkins.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.96,1:25:04.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NJust to go back to kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.37,1:25:14.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NWe were at lunch this afternoon, and we were all in disagreement on calibrating by 150
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.37,1:25:16.37,Default,,0,0,0,,points.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.37,1:25:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the next question.\NYou're not too good at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.37,1:25:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NBut the point was none of us were, and I've been playing with this for 20 years, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.40,1:25:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,with applied kinesiology.\NNow, the question is that, apart from just calibrating, you know, if I give, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.23,1:25:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,five members in the audience 10 or 20 yes or no questions to which we have yes or no\Nanswers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:42.23,1:25:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NThey won't agree.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:44.23,1:25:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They won't agree.\NAnd how many of them will get 19 out of 20 right?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.23,1:25:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Or even 10 out of 20 right?\NSo, then the next question that becomes is what about the reliability of the test?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:48.23,1:25:50.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because before we put our arm out here and test for something, you've got to make sure\Nthe ruler is.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.23,1:25:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can answer it, because I know your whole lecture.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:52.23,1:25:54.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has to do with internal consistency.\NThat every two people have to be able to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:54.23,1:25:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo, the question is, what about the reliability of the test?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:56.23,1:25:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because before we put our arm out here and test for something, you've got to make sure\Nthe ruler is.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.23,1:26:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I can answer it, because I know your whole lecture.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:04.23,1:26:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That every two people will maybe vary from another two people, but they will be internally\Nconsistent.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:10.19,1:26:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NNow, there's a proficiency and a skill.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:15.44,1:26:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Very few people, why were you doing this at lunch?\NI know why you were doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.86,1:26:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why you're getting varying answers already.\NI already got why you're doing it at lunch.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.96,1:26:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I wasn't doing it.\NI was on looking as two other people were doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.75,1:26:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's how it all came up.\NNot by you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.75,1:26:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm using the generic term.\NThe group.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:33.75,1:26:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah.\NI don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.67,1:26:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know the basics of kinesiology all the time.\NYour intention has to be to just know the truth of a thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.39,1:26:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't have any gain in it.\NYou can't be out to try to prove or disprove that kinesiology works or is accurate.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:51.11,1:26:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, so many people come at it with a challenge.\NThe minute you come at it with a challenge, you just blew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.53,1:27:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a very simple thing.\NI showed it so simply that it seems to me, you know, you've got to be really, really
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.57,1:27:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,stupid to not get it.\NI'm going to show it one more time.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.70,1:27:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to show it one last time.\NAnd if one more person brings up a question about kinesiology, I'm going to throw them
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.26,1:27:20.12,Default,,0,0,0,,into the pits.\NGood God.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:20.12,1:27:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's so dumb.\NGive me your arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:37.03,1:27:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the top picture and now resist.\NLook at the top picture and now resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.29,1:27:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the bottom picture.\NNow resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.01,1:27:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, Jesus, you don't have to go to college, do you?\NTo make it any more complicated than that is deliberate confusion.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.60,1:28:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That they project onto it because they want to adopt some kind of an argumentative position.\NForget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.43,1:28:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You just saw the truth of it.\NEnd of the problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.65,1:28:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But did you see, it's not, I mean, you know, it's not as simple or as easy as that.\NOh, it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.55,1:28:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's what you think.\NIt is as simple as that.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.55,1:28:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NThe point is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:13.55,1:28:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, he missed the point altogether, I see.\NYou want to turn it into an intellectual understanding?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.86,1:28:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.21,1:28:21.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.21,1:28:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:23.21,1:28:25.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.21,1:28:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.21,1:28:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:29.40,1:28:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NNo, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.40,1:28:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NWhat is your problem?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:33.40,1:28:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no.\NMy question is.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.40,1:28:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOn a clinical setting.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.40,1:28:41.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, I deal with chronic pain.\NWe've done studies on this.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.40,1:28:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, so I've been with this for 20 years.\NSo I'm not just asking about it flippantly.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:47.40,1:28:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is that how does it become consistent?\NHow do you not let your own bias fly into the test?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.40,1:28:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just what I got through telling you.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.40,1:28:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't have a bias.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:58.40,1:29:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But it sometimes creeps in without even knowing it's creeping in.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:01.40,1:29:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's when the test becomes wrong.\NOh, that's a matter of integrity.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.40,1:29:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why people over, under 200 can't do it.\NYou know that people under 200 cannot be integrists?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.40,1:29:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They cannot make a statement without having a position about it.\NIt's not possible because they're wrong brain physiology from the left brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:07.40,1:29:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they try to imitate it, they always get a falsehood because they're supposed to.\NIt's only when you get over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:09.40,1:29:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So when they try to imitate it, they always get a falsehood because they're supposed to.\NIt's only when you get over 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.23,1:29:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NSo when they try to imitate it, they always get a falsehood because they're supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.12,1:29:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when you get over 200.\NCan you adopt the positionality?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.12,1:29:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you vote for, let's say, a party that you think is the best for the government instead\Nof a party that's best for me?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:44.85,1:29:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200, I vote for him because he's going to be good to the cab drivers.\NOver 200, I vote for the mayor that I think is going to be the best for the city.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:55.03,1:29:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the difference.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.22,1:29:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:00.99,1:30:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we've got to stop.\NThey'll throw us out.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.37,1:30:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Be quick.\NBe quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.37,1:30:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I'll be quick.\NWe'll answer you quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.24,1:30:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NActually, I'm afraid of being thrown into the pits now.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.43,1:30:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-oh.\NNow you might get it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.43,1:30:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is regarding just research, the kind of research that you do.\NDo you typically calibrate things yourself and have teams confirm it?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.43,1:30:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you just stick with what you know?\NWell, we do it all different kinds of ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.43,1:30:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been doing it for some 25, 30 years.\NAnd I learned it from other people who were already doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.43,1:30:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't invent it.\NSo what's the method that you're using now?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.43,1:30:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've been doing it for some 25, 30 years.\NAnd I learned it from other people who were already doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.43,1:30:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't invent it.\NSo what's the method that you're using now?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.43,1:30:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we do it all different kinds of ways.\NWe've been doing it for some 25, 30 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.43,1:30:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And I learned it from other people who were already doing it.\NI didn't invent it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:28.43,1:30:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the method that you're using now?\NI just demonstrated it.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.43,1:30:32.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I just got through demonstrating it.\NNo, I'm just talking about like with other people.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.43,1:30:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you, you know, having it confirmed or what's the method you use for confirmation?\NI don't know if I want confirmation.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.43,1:30:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to know what somebody else gets because they're then running, see, it runs\Non your own scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:36.59,1:30:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you know, I don't know if I want confirmation.\NI don't want to know what somebody else gets because they're then running, see, it runs
Dialogue: 0,1:30:54.60,1:30:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,on your own scale.\NSo you can adopt any scale you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.40,1:31:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You can say 10 is true and 1 is not true and 5 is halfway between.\NYou can set up your own scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.66,1:31:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThen you will be integrous within your own scale, but not in my scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.45,1:31:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,If I set the barometric pressure as normal, so-and-so.\NSo if I have a different thermometer, if I say on my thermometer 0 is freezing and 212
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.45,1:31:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,is boiling, then that, on that thermometer, I will get that.\NYou can make your own thermometer and you'll get different figures.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:30.45,1:31:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSo you couldn't have people use your scale?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.77,1:31:35.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NOther people use our scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.77,1:31:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, you know, based on this scale of 1 to 1,000, you know, this calibrates it,\Nso-and-so.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.32,1:31:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see how you could get disparities if you're doing it integrously.\NI went to a lecture recently and they were saying that you use teams to...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.32,1:31:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.\NWell, because if you do it this way, yeah, you can also do it, you know, the O-ring.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.38,1:31:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't need a team.\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.38,1:32:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo if I hold Abraham Lincoln in mind, I'm going to hold Abraham Lincoln in mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.38,1:32:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NNow I'm holding somebody else in mind who says, we worship death.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:15.46,1:32:22.58,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no comparison.\NThe moment I hold this image in mind, I can't, I've got no strength.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:22.58,1:32:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I hold Abraham Lincoln in mind, it's simple.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:27.19,1:32:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it by yourself.\NYou don't have to worry about teams.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:29.19,1:32:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Teams.\NYou just have people who work together and they get intuitively aligned with each other
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.18,1:32:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and they can work very fast, you know.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:39.27,1:32:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:41.27,1:32:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes spouses can't work together for unknown reasons and the two of them have\Nto find a second, another person.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:48.13,1:32:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you get disparity, try working with yourself for a while until you get consistency.\NThere's a simpler method which I also explained last time and that's the end of the questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:59.52,1:33:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be a genius to do this.\NYou lift the dictionary.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.52,1:33:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You hold Abraham Lincoln in mind, you know, big heavy dictionary.\NAnd you see how much strength it takes to lift the dictionary with Abraham Lincoln.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.52,1:33:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you hold Bin Laden in mind and see how much strength it takes.\NYou'll see a marked difference.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:17.52,1:33:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you don't have to go to college.\NYou don't have to be a, you know, advanced physicist to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.12,1:33:30.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple.\NBecause it's so simple, that's why it's hard to see.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.24,1:33:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And in doing that, I would get my own level of truth with regards to that.\NObviously, I might not get your level of truth because we're in different places.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:38.08,1:33:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm a little bit more interested in yours than I am in mine.\NYou can say on a level of one to a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:46.08,1:33:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, according to this scale, this statement calibrates to start with as true or not true.\NAnd then you can try to get a number.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:56.08,1:34:00.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget we've done it thousands of times.\NDon't forget that I'm extremely intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.08,1:34:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see the essence of a thing before it speaks.\NSo, I mean, I've already got the number in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.08,1:34:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't tell her what the number is.\NYou know, we'll bring up something like this in my mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:10.17,1:34:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As I raise my hand, I've got, it's about 480 in my, you know, just a knowingness.\NI don't tell her what I'm holding in mind, but it says the number.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:18.17,1:34:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And then she gets to 480.\NIt just confirms.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.17,1:34:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean I'm accurate all the time.\NI trained myself to know the temperature.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.17,1:34:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I got an 84 caddy.\NAnd the thing I liked about it best, other than the fact that it's low down and gorgeous,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.17,1:34:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,.\NJust got repainted, oh boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.17,1:34:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got a thermometer.\NYou push the button, it tells you the outside temperature.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.17,1:34:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So I trained myself, because I had to get up every morning in the dark and the cold and drive.\NAnd I trained myself to say what the temperature is before I hit the button.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.17,1:34:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I found within a matter of months, I was so accurate,\NI could predict the temperature outside within a degree or two almost 99% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.49,1:35:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd go out to the car, and I would just know it's 64.\NI'd hit the button, it'd be 64.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:02.71,1:35:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I did that over and over again to train myself.\NAnd I did it as an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:07.71,1:35:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then once you were trained, you knew you were trained, and you didn't need to be prepared.\NSo, yes, I trained myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:12.71,1:35:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, I could tell the temperature within a matter of degrees.\NSo that's just experiential.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:19.12,1:35:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,See what I'm saying there?\NIt's experiential.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:22.12,1:35:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Trial and error.\NAnd we've got to get out of here at 530, they say.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.12,1:35:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.\NIf you make it very fast, I mean by very fast, get to the essence of it quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:31.12,1:35:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Want a picture?\NDo it quick.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.12,1:35:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What?\NDon't lag.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:35.12,1:35:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't drag.\NJump along.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:38.22,1:35:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Step lively.\NStep lively.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:40.22,1:35:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Slip lively.\NSlip lively.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.22,1:35:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Blast.\NSlip lively, or it's the gangplank for you.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:52.58,1:35:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's it.\NYou're the last, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.58,1:36:01.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, quick question.\NSince we're talking about spiritual teachers, and you didn't have that other list that you mentioned.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:01.58,1:36:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NI was wondering if,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.58,1:36:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because I've been following this path for a long time, for about 10 years.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.58,1:36:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,For the cryon energy, and the cryon channelings.\NI want to know what they ...
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.03,1:36:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a big, that's an entity on the other side?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.34,1:36:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I don't do channelers from the other side.\NBut it's interdimensional, and I've been following that path, and it says a lot of the same things you've been saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.00,1:36:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, good.\NYeah, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:30.00,1:36:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No more of you asking me.\NSo I want to know if it's higher or lower, or what.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:37.00,1:36:44.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's legitimate to ask that.\NThe essence of the spiritual truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:44.82,1:36:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's, for me, should I follow it anymore?\NI'm sincere in what I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.82,1:36:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We can ask that one.\NYou can ask that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:52.82,1:36:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It would be ...\NWe have permission to ask the question.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.82,1:37:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for her to continue with this teacher, resist.\NYou asked.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.77,1:37:13.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, thank you.\NI'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:13.08,1:37:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Come up.\NI'll tell you what happens.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:16.08,1:37:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there ...\NThere's nothing wrong with following things that don't calibrate real high, because they serve a purpose up to a certain point.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:24.52,1:37:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to make a lot of mistakes.\NSometimes, you know ...
Dialogue: 0,1:37:28.52,1:37:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And it serves a purpose, because after all, first of all, you're intended for ...\NIt was her spiritual integrity that drove her to the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.52,1:37:41.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the teacher that has the spiritual integrity.\NIt's the student.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:41.97,1:37:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,They follow all kinds of crooks out of their own inner honesty.\NCome on, baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:47.32,1:37:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This is God's love.\NLet's be godly.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:50.32,1:37:56.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it happens every day.\NWomen write books on, you know, gurus I've been seduced by.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:56.32,1:37:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a book.\NI've got them at home.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.32,1:38:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the story about all the gurus and the rap that he gave her.\NIt was her sincerity, her integrity, her honesty, her innocence that was ravished, you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.39,1:38:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think a teacher, you know, doesn't have to calibrate a 900 to be useful.\NYou can follow a false teacher for a while.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.39,1:38:19.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you've learned a lot.\NYou've learned a lot.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:19.39,1:38:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you've learned how to be a devotee.\NYou've learned self-sacrifice.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.39,1:38:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You've learned humility.\NAnd now you move to a higher teacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:27.39,1:38:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But, so ...\NYes, higher teachers and myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.86,1:38:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a question here with an email answer in case I didn't get up here.\NWhat?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.86,1:38:48.86,Default,,0,0,0,,My question is, why is Mary Baker Eddy not a part of the significant spiritual leadership\Nyou calibrate?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:48.86,1:38:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I picked more ancient ones.\NMary Baker Eddy, of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.86,1:38:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Four of her students.\NJoel Goldsmith.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.86,1:38:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yes.\NPhil Morris.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:58.86,1:39:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I forget.\NI don't know why.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:00.86,1:39:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably just prejudice against women, you know.\NThat's what I thought.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:09.28,1:39:11.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I know her name wasn't ...\NI thought there must be a really good reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.28,1:39:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No, because, you know, you have to know how we put this together.\NThat's 144, but we had hundreds, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.28,1:39:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I think we just took every sixth name or something like that off of her.\NI forget.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:25.28,1:39:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary Baker Eddy.\NWell, you know, she founded the church.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:27.28,1:39:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She founded ...\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:29.28,1:39:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And ...\NWhat, are you fishing for, or what?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:31.28,1:39:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No.\NThe Christian Science Monitor is a world-renowned ...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.28,1:39:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.\NMy grandmother was a Christian scientist.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.28,1:39:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Christian Science Monitor magazine, you know, calibrates quite high.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:41.28,1:39:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's just an outstanding group of people and movement.\NYes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.28,1:39:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why, you know, I think ...\NShe began the whole New Thought movement, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.28,1:39:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,She should be, she ought to be calibrated.\NI'd be very interested.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:49.28,1:39:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary Baker Eddy?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:51.28,1:39:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do Mary Baker Eddy.\NShe's got her upside, she's got her downside.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:53.28,1:40:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We have permission to do Mary, we don't have permission to do her.\NNo, come on, I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:01.83,1:40:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary Baker Eddy.\NWe have permission to do Mary Baker Eddy.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.87,1:40:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary Baker Eddy is over 200.\NThat's all you really need to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:14.23,1:40:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,She's over 300.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.23,1:40:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,She's over 300, 400, 500, 550, 560.\NNo, I'm getting false answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:23.41,1:40:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting false answers?\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.19,1:40:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the crowd and the answer.\NI can't answer accurately right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:28.67,1:40:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all laughing and stuff like that.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.81,1:40:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, well, thank you.\NShe's a good person.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:35.92,1:40:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,My grandmother was a Christian scientist, yes.\NShe used to read me Shakespeare, Christian science,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:44.24,1:40:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and take me to the Baptist church.\NIn the meantime, my grandfather was a Mason,
Dialogue: 0,1:40:51.44,1:40:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so I got it heavy from all sides, you know.\NDid you good.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.92,1:41:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's the dedication to the truth that you get out of it,\Nthe pristine nature of truth itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:05.64,1:41:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how it's expressed varies from teacher to teacher,\Nfrom era to era, from culture to culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:10.70,1:41:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But once you begin to value truth for its own sake,\Nbecause truth is one of the qualities of divinity,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:20.19,1:41:27.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you can follow then the love of truth and become devoted to truth.\NSo devotional non-duality is devoted to,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:27.17,1:41:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is the devotion to reaching the ultimate truth\Nthat is knowable within this dimension.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:33.34,1:41:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I want to thank you for the loveliness of this afternoon.\NWe want to congratulate the new couple.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:56.77,1:42:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So we say, Gloria in excelsis Deo.\NYou are God's gift to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:03.03,1:43:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.\NThe child in us never dies, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:43:11.64,1:43:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day is kindergarten to me.\NEvery day you discover something new and joyful about the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:23.53,1:43:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
